Video Game Mini Map
===================

This project is a fork of Video_Game_Mini_Maps by Garage Tinkering
(https://github.com/garagetinkering/Video_Game_Mini_Maps), which is
distributed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial license
(CC BY-NC), declared in its README:

  "Code is free to use and modify as you like, but not for commercial
   CC BY-NC (Attribution-NonCommercial)"

This fork and all modifications are therefore also licensed under
CC BY-NC 4.0: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/

You are free to share and adapt this code with attribution, for
non-commercial purposes only.

Third-party components under their own licenses
------------------------------------------------

- boards/esp32_s3_touch_amoled_1_8 - Waveshare ESP32-S3-Touch-AMOLED-1.8
  BSP (vendored + patched): Apache License 2.0 (see LICENSE in that
  directory)
- tools/map_generator - osm-game-tiles renderer
  (github.com/detoxity/osm-game-tiles), git submodule: MIT License
- tools/map_tiles - LVGL map tile converter by Eric Nam (0015),
  git submodule: MIT License (see LICENSE in the submodule)
- managed_components/ - Espressif and LVGL components fetched by the IDF
  component manager, each under its own license (Apache-2.0 / MIT)

Map data
--------

Map tiles are rendered from OpenStreetMap data, (c) OpenStreetMap
contributors, available under the Open Database License (ODbL):
https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright
Tile sets generated with tools/map_generator inherit the ODbL
attribution requirement.
